The data shows Luxembourg in second place at $128,200, Monaco at $115,700, and Ireland at $115,300 - all lower than Singapore's figure.
While Wikipedia's nominal GDP per capita rankings show different leaders (Monaco, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg), these are nominal values that don't account for cost of living adjustments.
The CIA data uses PPP (Purchasing Power Parity) adjustments, which provides a more accurate comparison of actual living standards between countries.
Singapore's position as #1 in real GDP per capita (PPP) is confirmed by the 2024 CIA World Factbook data, which is a reliable source.
